seriesStmt.title: Gregor Joseph Werner: A thematic catalogue of his works

annot.p: da capo of the respective movement in Sanctus

titlePage.label: [wrapper]
titlePage.p: S. Meſse in C | v. Grg Werner.

annot.p: S solo and coro (9), A solo and coro (9), T solo and coro (9), B solo and coro (10), clno 1 (6), clno 2 (4), timp (4), vl 1 (2x; 14, 14), vl 2 (2x; 13, 13), vlne (11), org (14)

A, clno 1, clno 2, timp, vlne, and org are autograph manuscripts; in S, T, and B, the title and keys in the first 4 lines are by Werner, while the remaining elements are by a different hand; vl 1 (2x) and vl 2 (2x) are entirely copies

titlePage.label: [wrapper]
titlePage.p:
Miſsa Solennis | St: Trinitatis. Ex C | Canto. Alto. | Tenor. Baſso | Violinis 2. | Clarinis 2. | Tympano. | con | Organo. [by different hand:] è Violone. | Authre Sigre Werner.
[above last line by different hand:] NB omne tulit punctum qui miscuit utile dulci: | aut certa modulos naturæ, lege ligavit. [the first line is verse 343 of the Ars poetica by Quintus Horatius Flaccus]

annot.p: S solo and coro (8), A solo and coro (8), T solo and coro (8), B solo and coro (10), clno 1 (4), clno 2 (4), timp (4), vl 1 (13), vl 2 (10), vlne (10), org (12)
